<Content>Well located, small, elegant We enjoyed our weekend stay in the Luxembourg Parc and think it deserves its four star rating.. The hotel is well located in the Latin Quarter, opposite the Senate and the Mus茅e de Luxembourg, close to St Germain but several minutes walk from the nearest M茅tro. The immediate area is quiet.This is a small hotel in many ways, a conversion of an old building. There are just 23 rooms, of varying sizes but generally quite small, and compact public areas. Our room was elegantly furnished in traditional style - including the original roof beams - and the only irritant was poor lighting (but not in the well equipped marble bathroom). There鈥檚 a library lounge, a bar, a fitness centre, an indoor courtyard, and a small breakfast room. There is no restaurant (but plenty of choice nearby). The staff were all pleasant and helpful and the overall experience relaxing. The breakfast is a good compromise between American and French tastes. There is a public computer and free WiFi.This hotel is a good choice for those who like their luxury understated and moderately priced for Paris. It鈥檚 certainly one of the best we have used in our many visits to that city. But it is small, a place for sleeping in rather than living in and probably better for a short stay.Tip - avoid the Taverne St Germain, the worst restaurant we have encountered for a long time, anywhere. 
